longBusinessSummary: Cerro de Pasco Resources Inc. engages in the acquisition and exploration of mineral properties. Its principal project is the 100% owned El Metalurgista mining concession that has sphalerite, tennantite, cerussite, enargite, galena, pyrite, chalcopyrite, and pyrrhotite metals covering an area of approximately 95.74 hectares located in Lima, Peru. The company is headquartered in Saint-Sauveur, Canada.
